|YKBThere have been several changes made to equipment on DarkWind. We
believe that in total, they will make for a more vibrant playstyle
for our players.

|WKBSaved Gear
|WKO==========

  |YKOYou will now save the gear you are carrying on you when you leave
  the game. If you're wearing/wielding equipment, you will wear/
  wield it when you re-enter the game.

  Not every item will be saved to your character, including the
  following items:
  |BKB -- |CKBGear that was previously donated, or is currently broken.
  |BKB -- |CKBFood and/or Drinks.
  |BKB -- |CKBUniques.
  |BKB -- |CKBAnything directly restricted by the immortals of DarkWind.
  |BKB -- |CKBAnything that you normally cannot drop on your own.
  |BKB -- |CKBAnything inside of a container (the container may save though)

  |YKOAny modifications to the equipment will also be stripped when you
  re-enter the game (harden, lighten, flaming, etc.).

  There is also a limit to the number of items that will safely
  be stored. It is many hundreds of items, and you would have
  to work to break it. Therefore, any items lost when you
  re-enter the game can not, and will not be refunded.

|WKBSLOTS
|WKO=====

  |YKOCharacters and monsters can wear equipment on the head, body,
  legs, hands, feet, shield arm, cloak/body, shoulders, aura, two
  fingers, and two neck slots. Ordinary rings and amulets will fill
  the first available matching slot.

  Use |YKOeq|WKO or |YKOmyeq|WKO to see what you are currently wearing,
  wielding, or using as active non-cybernetic internal equipment.
  Strength and level both help determine how much gear you can carry
  before becoming encumbered.

|WKBITEM LEVEL
|WKO==========

  |YKOEquipment may have an item level showing where it belongs in game
  progression. Ranked weapons penetrate part of the physical protection from
  lower-level worn armour; ranked armour gains protection against lower-level
  weapons. Equal-level ratings cancel. Item level is not automatically a
  minimum character level—actual restrictions are listed separately. Most
  equipment found in a cataloged area inherits the midpoint of that area's
  recommended level range; special rewards may use their own level. Monsters
  fighting with natural attacks or intrinsic armour use their monster level
  when no effective weapon or worn armour supplies an item level.
